Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.81,1:15:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望你们别再给我太多麻烦了\N{\rEn}I wish you would stop causing me so much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.31,1:15:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托\N{\rEn}Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.26,1:15:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们这岁数...\N{\rEn}At our age...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.49,1:15:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...我们不该走那么远，在这大热天\N{\rEn}...we shouldn't be traveling so far in this heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.25,1:15:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而灰尘...\N{\rEn}And the dust...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.24,1:16:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今年更糟\N{\rEn}Especially bad this year.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.85,1:16:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一切都没必要\N{\rEn}And it's all so unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.50,1:16:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只需用一点功夫...\N{\rEn}Just make a little effort...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.37,1:16:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...即可明白我们的意图\N{\rEn}...to understand our point of view.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.56,1:16:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不恨你们\N{\rEn}We don't hate you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.59,1:16:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们自己背上麻烦\N{\rEn}You've brought it on yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.00,1:16:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们也能...\N{\rEn}And you can...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.20,1:16:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...自己摆脱它\N{\rEn}...rid yourselves of it too.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.20,1:16:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没必要感到迷惑\N{\rEn}No need to feel lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.33,1:16:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会给你们时间想个明白\N{\rEn}I'll give you time to think it over.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.88,1:16:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后你们能给我个明理的答复\N{\rEn}Then you can give me a reasonable answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.81,1:16:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带走\N{\rEn}Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.50,1:17:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，不是你\N{\rEn}No, not you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.20,1:17:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你留下\N{\rEn}You stay!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.50,1:17:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你理解，我对他们说的吗\N{\rEn}You understood, what I was saying to them?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.44,1:17:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的日语够好吗\N{\rEn}Your Japanese is good enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.97,1:17:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看到你的眼睛\N{\rEn}I saw your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.51,1:17:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么？你以为你从那儿看到了什么\N{\rEn}What? And what did you think you saw there?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.80,1:17:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们是傻瓜，农民\N{\rEn}They are fools, the peasants.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.05,1:17:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主啊，赦免他们的苦难，以您之手护其平安\N{\rEn}Lord, spare them suffering and keep them safe in your hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.05,1:17:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们能跟人高谈阔论不休却决断全无\N{\rEn}They can talk a man down south without end and decide nothing!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.92,1:17:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你明白，不是吗？\N{\rEn}But you understand, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.73,1:17:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直接说你啥意思\N{\rEn}Just say what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.21,1:18:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一切全取决于你...\N{\rEn}That it all depends on you...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.70,1:18:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...他们是否获释\N{\rEn}...whether they are set free.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.00,1:18:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你只说一个词\N{\rEn}If you say just one single word,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.57,1:18:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...示范他们，否定你的信仰\N{\rEn}...show them, deny your faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.76,1:18:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以若我拒绝，你杀了我\N{\rEn}So what if I refuse, you kill me?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.99,1:18:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,殉道者之血乃教会之种苗\N{\rEn}The blood of martyrs is the seed of the Church.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.20,1:18:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有如那些传教士...\N{\rEn}Just like the priests...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.80,1:18:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...你屠杀于大村、长崎的\N{\rEn}...you slaughtered in Omora, Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.60,1:18:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们从错误中学到了\N{\rEn}- We learned from our mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.85,1:18:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,处决传教士及处死农民让事情更糟\N{\rEn}Killing the priests and killing the peasants makes it worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.38,1:18:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若他们能为神而死...\N{\rEn}If they can die for their God...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.60,1:18:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...他们只会认为这能使他们更坚强\N{\rEn}...they think it only makes them stronger.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.27,1:18:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若你觉得有必要惩罚某人，单独惩罚我\N{\rEn}If you feel you must punish someone, punish me alone!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.00,1:18:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你！说得不像是个好传教士\N{\rEn}You! Do not speak like a good priest.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.38,1:18:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你是真实的男人\N{\rEn}If you are a real man
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.50,1:18:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真正好的传教士\N{\rEn}a truly good priest.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.60,1:18:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该同情基督徒\N{\rEn}You should feel pity for the Christian.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.50,1:19:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不该那样吗？神父，不该那样吗\N{\rEn}Isn't that so, Padre, isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.09,1:19:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你荣耀的代价，是他们的苦难\N{\rEn}The price for your glory is their suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.00,1:19:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 神父？\N{\rEn}- Padre?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.00,1:19:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 赞美神，吾等之父\N{\rEn}- Praise be to God our Father.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.32,1:19:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赞美他\N{\rEn}Praise be to Him.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.63,1:19:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,葡萄牙语是个礼物...\N{\rEn}The Portuguese language was a gift...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.00,1:19:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...来自你们的神父卡布拉尔\N{\rEn}...of your Father Cabral.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.44,1:19:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我被派做你的翻译\N{\rEn}I've been asked to interpret on your behalf.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.48,1:20:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,考虑到我们可能需要你证词的一些微妙之处\N{\rEn}There was concern that we might need certain subtleties in your testimony,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.00,1:20:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你被告知只能说日语\N{\rEn}if you were told to speak only in Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.54,1:20:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,证词？我...\N{\rEn}The testimony, I...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.10,1:20:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们希望它是公平的\N{\rEn}We want it to be fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.50,1:20:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,且我们已更好地掌握你们的语言...\N{\rEn}and we'd have a better grasp of your language
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.38,1:20:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...胜过你们掌握我们的\N{\rEn}...than you do of ours.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.00,1:20:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父卡布拉尔从未说过比“感谢神”更多\N{\rEn}Father Cabral never managed much more than "Arigataya".
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.00,1:20:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a12}{\rTop_cn}Arigataya[ありがたや]，词汇原意指罕见的事。有好事发生时，当对神说这话。值得庆幸之意
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.86,1:20:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他住这儿的日子\N{\rEn}All the time he lived here.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.94,1:20:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他只教不学\N{\rEn}He taught, but would not learn.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.30,1:20:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他鄙视我们的语言、我们的食物、我们的习惯\N{\rEn}He despised our language, our food, our customs.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.07,1:20:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟他不一样，我不像卡布拉尔\N{\rEn}I'm not like him, I'm not like Cabral.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.98,1:20:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 真的？- 是的\N{\rEn}- Really? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.68,1:20:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有自己的宗教信仰，神父\N{\rEn}We have our own religion, Padre.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.20,1:20:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜你没有注意到它\N{\rEn}Pity you did not notice it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.51,1:20:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，不\N{\rEn}No, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.80,1:20:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们只是思考的方式不同\N{\rEn}We just think a different way.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.63,1:20:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的\N{\rEn}True.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.00,1:20:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你相信我们的佛只是凡人\N{\rEn}You believe our Buddhas are only men.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.00,1:20:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是人类\N{\rEn}Just human beings.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.48,1:20:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使佛，也会死\N{\rEn}Even a Buddha dies.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.00,1:20:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟所有人一样，他...\N{\rEn}Like all men, he is...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.40,1:20:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...不是造物主。- 你不懂\N{\rEn}...not the creator. - You are ignorant!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.70,1:21:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父，只有基督徒把佛看得如凡人简单\N{\rEn}Padre, only a Christian would see Buddha simply as a man.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.98,1:21:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的佛是存在的\N{\rEn}Our Buddha is a being.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.50,1:21:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,此乃人可以成为比其本身更伟大者\N{\rEn}Which men can become something greater than himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.78,1:21:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若他能克服其一切妄念\N{\rEn}If he can overcome all his illusions.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.67,1:21:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你坚持你的妄念...\N{\rEn}But you cling to your illusions...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.00,1:21:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...还称之为信仰\N{\rEn}...and call them faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.60,1:21:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，你不懂\N{\rEn}No, you don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.00,1:21:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,任何人只要遵从神的嘱咐\N{\rEn}If any man follows God's commandments.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.29,1:21:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他就能过上平静快乐的生活\N{\rEn}Then he can live a peaceful and joyous life!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.66,1:21:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我懂！我明白\N{\rEn}I do! I do understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.60,1:21:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父，这太简单了\N{\rEn}Padre, it is perfectly simple!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.72,1:21:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Korobu."\N{\rEn}転ぶ
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.02,1:21:32.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你听过那词吗\N{\rEn}Have you heard that word?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.02,1:21:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Korobu."\N{\rEn}転ぶ
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.69,1:21:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它意思是塌下，放弃\N{\rEn}It means fall down. Surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.65,1:21:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放弃信仰，弃教，如你所说\N{\rEn}Give up the faith, apostatize, as you say.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.52,1:21:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做吧\N{\rEn}Do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.14,1:21:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你不弃教\N{\rEn}If you don't apostatize.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.80,1:21:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,囚犯们会被挂起“穴吊”\N{\rEn}The prisoners will be hang over the Pit.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.54,1:21:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到你弃教，你们的命随血流，\N{\rEn}Until you do, your life's bleeding away,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.10,1:21:55.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...一滴连一滴\N{\rEn}...drop by drop.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.48,1:21:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些持续几天，有些不行\N{\rEn}Some last for days, some do not.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.00,1:22:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们死了\N{\rEn}They die.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.56,1:22:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们折磨神父斯伯罗和卡索拉\N{\rEn}They tortured Father Sporo and Kasora.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.10,1:22:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,穴吊\N{\rEn}Over the Pit.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.50,1:22:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你听说过他们吗\N{\rEn}Have you heard of them?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.18,1:22:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有个叫神父图姆\N{\rEn}There was one called Pedro Tomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.75,1:22:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有费雷拉，当然\N{\rEn}And Ferreira, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.50,1:22:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费雷拉\N{\rEn}Ferreira?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.57,1:22:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认识他\N{\rEn}Did you knew him?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.87,1:22:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听过他\N{\rEn}I've heard of him.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.54,1:22:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毫无疑问，他现在在全日本都很有名\N{\rEn}No doubt, he's well-known all over Japan now.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.40,1:22:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“有着日本名及日本妻的传教士。”\N{\rEn}"The Priest with a Japanese name and a Japanese wife."
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.55,1:22:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不信。- 你可问任何人\N{\rEn}I don't believe. - You can ask anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.00,1:22:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长崎的人提到他就惊叹\N{\rEn}People in Nagasaki point him out and marvel.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.53,1:22:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他如今身份很高\N{\rEn}He is helding great steam now.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.04,1:22:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是为何，我相信他首先会来这儿\N{\rEn}Which is why，I believe he came here in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.24,1:22:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,傲慢的人。像他们所有人\N{\rEn}Arrogant man. Like all of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.79,1:22:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这意味着他最终会屈服\N{\rEn}Which means he'll eventually fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.40,1:23:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为殉教会成为我的救赎\N{\rEn}I thought that martyrdom would be my salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.69,1:23:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恳求神。别让它成为我的耻辱\N{\rEn}Please God. Do not let it be my shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.63,1:23:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看啦！他好高\N{\rEn}Look! He's so big!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.35,1:23:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何你要跟着我\N{\rEn}Why are you following me?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.71,1:23:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别跟着我\N{\rEn}Stop following me!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.60,1:24:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感谢主，赐予温和的日子于此处\N{\rEn}Thank you Lord for the gentle days here.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.69,1:24:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 主教导我要爱每个人\N{\rEn}- Jesus taught me to love everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.82,1:24:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 但我不能感到爱，对那些\N{\rEn}- But I can not feel love to those who
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.60,1:24:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 把我们的朋友折磨致死的人\N{\rEn}- torture our friends to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.36,1:24:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我愤怒，我不能爱他们\N{\rEn}- I am angry. I can not love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.04,1:24:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连卫兵都被你的手碰过，主\N{\rEn}Even the guards have been touched by your hand, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.04,1:24:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我感到有罪\N{\rEn}- I feel guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.54,1:24:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想知道是否这连日的平静已证明\N{\rEn}I wonder if this unbroken peace is proof...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.80,1:24:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我的死不远了\N{\rEn}- That my death is not far away.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.80,1:24:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,永不动摇\N{\rEn}Shall never be shaken.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.00,1:24:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,永不动摇\N{\rEn}Shall never be shaken.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.83,1:24:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看到您儿子的命运，如此清晰，有如我自己的\N{\rEn}I see the life of your son so clearly, almost like my own.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.00,1:25:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有他的脸\N{\rEn}And his face...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.80,1:25:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它带走了我的所有恐惧\N{\rEn}it takes all fear from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.96,1:25:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它就是那张我儿时便记得的脸\N{\rEn}It is the face that I remember from childhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.48,1:25:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对我说着话\N{\rEn}Speaking to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.17,1:25:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我确信这点\N{\rEn}I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.90,1:25:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,承诺着我不会放弃你\N{\rEn}Promising I will not abandon you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.40,1:25:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会放弃你\N{\rEn}I will not abandon you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.75,1:25:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会放弃你\N{\rEn}I will not abandon you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.71,1:25:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,穿上它们\N{\rEn}Put them on.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.38,1:25:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你该感到荣幸，这是我们的传教士(指和尚)穿的\N{\rEn}You should be honored, it is what our priests wear.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.29,1:25:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父罗德里格斯，来自葡萄牙，是吗\N{\rEn}Padre Rodriguez from Portugal, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.94,1:25:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很抱歉，神父，为我说的话\N{\rEn}I am sorry, Padre, for my speaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.68,1:26:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的语言不太好\N{\rEn}My language is not so good
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.50,1:26:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...但是藩主...\N{\rEn}...but His Lordship...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.20,1:26:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...筑后奉行...\N{\rEn}...the governor of Chikuwo...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.20,1:26:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...担心关于...\N{\rEn}...is anxious about...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.96,1:26:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...你的...适...适应...\N{\rEn}...Your are com...comfort...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.00,1:26:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...适应\N{\rEn}...Comfort.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.80,1:26:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 也许不适应\N{\rEn}- Perhaps discomfort.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.49,1:26:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不适应，是的\N{\rEn}Discomfort, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.84,1:26:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,关于你为何到此\N{\rEn}About why you are here
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.60,1:26:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你不自在\N{\rEn}and if you are not at ease
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.84,1:26:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请说出来\N{\rEn}please say so.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.52,1:26:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你旅途遥远\N{\rEn}Your trip was long.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.40,1:26:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,危险众多\N{\rEn}There were many dangers.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.26,1:26:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你决心的力量极大的触动了我们\N{\rEn}The power of your determination touches us greatly.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.30,1:26:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们知你已受苦甚巨\N{\rEn}We know you have already suffered greatly.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.10,1:26:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不希望再增你的苦难\N{\rEn}We do not wish to add to your suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.07,1:26:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使我们可能这样做\N{\rEn}And the thought that we might do so
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.40,1:26:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...也使我们痛苦\N{\rEn}...is painful for us too.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.00,1:26:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEn}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.78,1:26:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父\N{\rEn}Padre.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.23,1:26:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你带来的教义...\N{\rEn}The doctrine you bring with you...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.23,1:27:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...在西班牙和葡萄牙可能是真的\N{\rEn}...may be true in Spain and Portugal.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.71,1:27:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们仔细研究过\N{\rEn}But we have studied it carefully.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.20,1:27:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,专心致志，积日累久\N{\rEn}So devotedly over much time.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.01,1:27:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们发现它在日本毫无用处，没有价值\N{\rEn}We find it is of no use and no value in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.80,1:27:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们断定它是危险之物\N{\rEn}We have concluded that it is a danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.82,1:27:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们相信，我们给你们带来了真理\N{\rEn}But we believe, we have brought you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.99,1:27:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而真理是普遍的\N{\rEn}And the truth is universal.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.68,1:27:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它对任何国家都是共同的，在任何时候。这就是为何我们称之为真理\N{\rEn}It's common to all countries, at all times. That's why we call it the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.65,1:27:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果教义在日本这儿不像在葡萄牙那么正确\N{\rEn}If a doctrine weren't as true here in Japan, as it is in Portugal.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.00,1:27:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么我们就不会称之为真理\N{\rEn}Then we couldn't call it the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.55,1:27:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看出你不用你的双手工作，神父\N{\rEn}I see that you do not work with your hands, Father.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.51,1:28:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但人人皆知，一棵树在某地茂盛茁壮\N{\rEn}But everyone knows a tree which flourishes in one kind of earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.00,1:28:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在别处可能腐烂死亡\N{\rEn}May decay and die in another.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.71,1:28:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这与天主教的树是一样的，叶烂于此\N{\rEn}It is the same with the tree of Christianity. The leaves decay here.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.31,1:28:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,芽遂亡\N{\rEn}The buds die.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.98,1:28:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是土壤杀死了芽\N{\rEn}It is not the soil that has killed the buds.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.12,1:28:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有叁拾万基督徒在日本这儿，在土壤...\N{\rEn}There were 300.000 Christians here in Japan, before the soil was...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.67,1:28:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎样\N{\rEn}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.63,1:28:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...中毒前\N{\rEn}...was poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.17,1:28:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没有回复吗？\N{\rEn}You have no reply?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.83,1:28:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你又何必？你永远不必去改变我的心\N{\rEn}Why should you? You're never going to change my heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.16,1:28:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就有如，我不必去改变你的\N{\rEn}And it seems like, I'm not going to change yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.48,1:29:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想测试我的信仰？给我一个真正的挑战\N{\rEn}You want to test my faith? Give me a real challenge!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.78,1:29:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带我去见奉行官\N{\rEn}Bring me to the Inquisitor!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.78,1:29:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带我...\N{\rEn}Bring me...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.09,1:29:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...去见井上大人\N{\rEn}...to Inoue Sama!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.34,1:29:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何他们要笑？\N{\rEn}Why are they laughing?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.00,1:29:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没说任何好笑的，为何他们要笑\N{\rEn}I didn't say anything funny, why are they laughing?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.51,1:29:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为，神父...\N{\rEn}Because Padre...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.08,1:29:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为\N{\rEn}Because.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.54,1:29:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就是筑后国的筑后守(官职名)\N{\rEn}I am the governor of Chikuwo.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.92,1:29:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就是奉行官\N{\rEn}I am the Inquisitor.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.07,1:29:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是，你知道吗\N{\rEn}I am, you know it?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.91,1:30:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多久？他们得这样干多久？在雨中\N{\rEn}How long? How long will they have to work like this in the rain?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.52,1:30:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到完工\N{\rEn}Until finished.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.50,1:30:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 神父！\N{\rEn}- Padre!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.40,1:30:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 神父\N{\rEn}- Padre!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.60,1:30:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 神父\N{\rEn}- Padre!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.30,1:30:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请听我说\N{\rEn}Please listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.89,1:31:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们威胁我\N{\rEn}They threatened me.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.11,1:31:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我从没拿过他们的钱\N{\rEn}- I never took their money!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.56,1:31:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没有为钱出卖你\N{\rEn}I did not betray you for money!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.51,1:31:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小心他，神父\N{\rEn}Be careful with him, Padre.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.50,1:31:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能井上大人雇他使我们踏踩\N{\rEn}Maybe Inoue Sama pays him to make us trample.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.12,1:31:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 不！他没有\N{\rEn}- No, he did not!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.77,1:32:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恳求神父，让我告解\N{\rEn}Please Padre, let me confess.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.00,1:32:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 神父\N{\rEn}- Padre.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.58,1:32:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知，我闻到了，我闻到了罪\N{\rEn}I know, I smell. I smell of sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.81,1:32:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想再次告解，主就会把我洗干净\N{\rEn}I want to confess again, so the Lord can wash me clean.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.80,1:32:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何你要来这儿？\N{\rEn}Why did you come here?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.13,1:32:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是为赎罪吗？\N{\rEn}Is it for absolution?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.80,1:32:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有任何赎罪是啥的认识吗？\N{\rEn}Do you have any understanding what absolution is?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.33,1:32:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你懂我正在说什么吗？\N{\rEn}Do you understand what I've been saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.25,1:32:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多年前，我可能会死为一个好基督徒\N{\rEn}Years ago, I could have died a good Christian.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.60,1:33:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有迫害\N{\rEn}There was no persecution.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.60,1:33:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何我生在现在？\N{\rEn}Why was I born now?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.20,1:33:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这太不公平\N{\rEn}This is so unfair!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.00,1:33:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起\N{\rEn}I am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.33,1:33:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还相信吗\N{\rEn}Do you still believe?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.72,1:33:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赐福我神父，我有罪啊\N{\rEn}Bless me Padre. For I have sinned.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.50,1:33:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我惭愧，因如此软弱\N{\rEn}I am sorry for being so weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.98,1:33:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我惭愧，这已经发生了\N{\rEn}I am sorry, this has happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.27,1:34:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我惭愧，因我对你所做的一切\N{\rEn}I am sorry for what I did to you!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.91,1:34:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,救救我，神父\N{\rEn}Help me, Padre.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.38,1:34:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,解除此罪\N{\rEn}Take away the sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.52,1:34:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会再次尝试要坚强\N{\rEn}I will try again to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.47,1:34:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天父，耶稣怎会爱一个卑鄙如此的人\N{\rEn}Father, how could Jesus love a wretch like this?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.11,1:34:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里到处都是邪恶，我感觉到它的力量，甚至它的美丽\N{\rEn}There is evil all around in this place, I sense its strength even its beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.18,1:34:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这个男人两者皆无\N{\rEn}But there is none of that in this man.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.73,1:34:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不配称为邪恶\N{\rEn}He is not worthy to be called evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.80,1:34:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安心去吧\N{\rEn}Go in peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.06,1:34:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得.. 我，我害怕.. 耶稣，原谅我\N{\rEn}I feel.. I, I fear.. Jesus, forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.20,1:34:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也许不值得您爱\N{\rEn}I may not be worthy of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.20,1:35:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只是个形式\N{\rEn}This is just a formality.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.80,1:35:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要一步就行\N{\rEn}Just one step will do.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.40,1:35:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不要求你真诚地去做\N{\rEn}We're not asking you to do it sincerely.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.10,1:35:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只须把你的脚放这东西上，不用背叛你的信仰\N{\rEn}Just putting your foot on the thing won't betray your faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.70,1:35:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会真的关心\N{\rEn}I don't really care.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.20,1:35:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你越早做...\N{\rEn}The sooner you do it...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.20,1:35:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...我们就越快避开太阳\N{\rEn}...the sooner we get out of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.20,1:35:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只需用你的脚轻轻地踩，若你愿意\N{\rEn}Just touch it with your foot lightly if you like.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.50,1:35:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管你愿意几何...\N{\rEn}However you like...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.20,1:35:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...你将会立即获释\N{\rEn}...and you'll be free immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.80,1:36:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它只是图片\N{\rEn}It's only a picture.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.90,1:36:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你脚放其上\N{\rEn}Put your foot on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.90,1:36:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马上\N{\rEn}Now!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.30,1:36:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下一个\N{\rEn}Next!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.60,1:36:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么样？\N{\rEn}How about you?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.30,1:36:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这绝无意义\N{\rEn}It is pointless.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.20,1:36:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马上\N{\rEn}Now!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.60,1:36:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下一个\N{\rEn}Next!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.10,1:37:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以轻轻地做\N{\rEn}You can do it lightly.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.30,1:37:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后你就自由了\N{\rEn}Then you will be free.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.70,1:37:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马上\N{\rEn}Now.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.50,1:37:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只需踏上它\N{\rEn}Just step on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.00,1:37:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前进\N{\rEn}Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.60,1:37:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下一个\N{\rEn}Next.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.30,1:37:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只一步\N{\rEn}Only one step.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.30,1:37:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马上...\N{\rEn}Now...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.30,1:37:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你肯定想获释\N{\rEn}You must want to be free.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.30,1:37:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,获释\N{\rEn}Be free!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.60,1:37:35.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你脚放其上\N{\rEn}Put your foot on it!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.70,1:38:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都带他们回去\N{\rEn}Take them all back.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.10,1:38:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,留下那个\N{\rEn}Leave that one behind.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.39,1:38:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢主听到我的祈祷\N{\rEn}Thank you Lord for hearing my prayer!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.10,1:40:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是基督徒的下场\N{\rEn}This is what happens to Christians!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.30,1:40:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是...\N{\rEn}But...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.80,1:40:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...我将向你们示范，一个如何避免那种命运的例子\N{\rEn}...I will show you an example of how to avoid that fate.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.60,1:40:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带他过来\N{\rEn}Bring him here.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.80,1:40:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前进\N{\rEn}Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.10,1:40:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把脚放上去\N{\rEn}Just put your foot there.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.10,1:40:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看这有多容易\N{\rEn}See how easy it is?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.80,1:40:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我承认他练习过\N{\rEn}I admit he's had practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.40,1:40:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但看看这动作多简单\N{\rEn}But look how simple the movement is.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.00,1:41:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它甚至没有鞠躬难\N{\rEn}It is not even as hard as bowing.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.90,1:41:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是吗\N{\rEn}Is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.30,1:41:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或跑步\N{\rEn}Or running.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.10,1:41:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马上滚\N{\rEn}Now go!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.30,1:41:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,滚出去\N{\rEn}Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.80,1:41:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们看见了吗\N{\rEn}You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.20,1:41:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他履行了他的义务\N{\rEn}He lived up to his obligation.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.60,1:41:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就这样\N{\rEn}That is all.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.80,1:42:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很抱歉，如今我已忽略你多日，神父\N{\rEn}I'm sorry I've neglected you for some days now, Padre.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.58,1:42:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在平户有些事\N{\rEn}But I had business in Hirado.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.30,1:42:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望有天你能亲自去那儿\N{\rEn}I hope you get to go there yourself sometime.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.16,1:42:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那里确实很漂亮\N{\rEn}Sure it's very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.62,1:42:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,传闻有个有趣故事，关于统治那儿的大名\N{\rEn}There lays an interesting story about the Dimeov who ruled there
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.68,1:42:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有四个侧室\N{\rEn}He had four concubines.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.79,1:42:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,四个\N{\rEn}Four.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.78,1:42:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们都漂亮，但她们...\N{\rEn}They were all beautiful, but they...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.06,1:42:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很抱歉\N{\rEn}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.00,1:43:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许这故事不应说与独身的传教士\N{\rEn}Maybe this is not a story for a celibate priest.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.47,1:43:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没关系，请继续\N{\rEn}It's alright, please go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.54,1:43:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那种情况下，大名的侧室都嫉妒\N{\rEn}In that case, the Dimeov's concubines were all jealous.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.65,1:43:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们斗来斗去没完没了\N{\rEn}And they fought and fought without end,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.00,1:43:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,于是平户大名赶她们出其城\N{\rEn}so the Dimeov Hirado drove them away from his castle.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.50,1:43:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安宁就再次来到他的生活\N{\rEn}And peace came into his life again.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.99,1:43:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为这故事有教训吗？\N{\rEn}Do you think this story has a lesson?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.54,1:43:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\rEn}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.37,1:43:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即这是个很明智的男人\N{\rEn}That this was a very wise man.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.69,1:43:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很高兴，那意味着你明白大名就像日本\N{\rEn}I'm glad. That means you understand the Dimeov is like Japan.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.98,1:43:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些侧室是西班牙，葡萄牙，荷兰，英格兰\N{\rEn}And these concubines are Spain, Portugal, Holland, England.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.00,1:43:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人人试图获得相对别人的优势\N{\rEn}Each trying to gain advantage against the other
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.20,1:43:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还在过程中摧毁了房子\N{\rEn}and destroy the house in the process.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.57,1:44:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,既然你说此人聪明，你就会明白\N{\rEn}Since you said this man is wise, you will understand
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.20,1:44:05.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...为何我们必须禁止天主教\N{\rEn}...why we must outlaw the Christians.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.31,1:44:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而，我们的教会教导一夫一妻\N{\rEn}Well. Our Church teaches monogamy.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.50,1:44:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个妻子\N{\rEn}One wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.04,1:44:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那如果日本在四人中选一个合法的妻子呢？\N{\rEn}What if Japan were to choose one lawful wife from the four?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.18,1:44:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你指葡萄牙\N{\rEn}You mean Portugal?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.63,1:44:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不\N{\rEn}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.74,1:44:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我指神圣的教堂\N{\rEn}I mean the Holy Church.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.40,1:44:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道你不认为这样好多了，男人忘记外国女人...\N{\rEn}Don't you think it would be better for the man to forget about foreign women...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.89,1:44:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...选一个他本国的\N{\rEn}...and choose one of his own?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.21,1:44:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国籍并不那么重要，当婚姻已至\N{\rEn}Nationality is not so important when it comes to a marriage.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.68,1:44:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...重要的是爱\N{\rEn}...what matters is love.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.50,1:44:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱和忠诚\N{\rEn}Love and fidelity.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.31,1:44:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱！\N{\rEn}Love!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.50,1:45:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父，也有男人被困扰于\N{\rEn}Padre, there are men who are plagued
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.00,1:45:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...丑女的痴情\N{\rEn}...by the persistent love of an ugly woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.96,1:45:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是传教工作对你的意义吗\N{\rEn}Is that what missionary work is to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.40,1:45:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,丑女？\N{\rEn}An ugly woman?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.13,1:45:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\rEn}Well.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.00,1:45:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\rEn}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.34,1:45:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们怎么称呼一个不能生孩子的女人\N{\rEn}How do you call a woman who cannot bear children?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.94,1:45:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不育\N{\rEn}Barren.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.00,1:45:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不育之女不能成为真正的妻子\N{\rEn}A barren woman can not be a true wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.85,1:45:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果福音在此迷失方向，那不是教会的错\N{\rEn}If the gospel has lost its way here, it is not the fault of the Church.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.77,1:45:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,错在那些强行把忠诚从其信仰拉开者\N{\rEn}It is the fault of those who tear away the faithful from their faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.07,1:45:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像丈夫从妻子\N{\rEn}like a husband from a wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.49,1:45:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你指...\N{\rEn}You mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.00,1:45:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...我\N{\rEn}...Me?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.46,1:45:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父，你们传教士似乎不懂日本\N{\rEn}Padre, your missionaries do not seem to know Japan!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.09,1:46:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而你，尊敬的奉行官，似乎不懂天主教\N{\rEn}And you, Honorable Inquisitor, do not seem to know Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.70,1:46:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些人认为你们的宗教是诅咒\N{\rEn}There are those who think of your religion as a curse.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.49,1:46:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不\N{\rEn}I do not.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.89,1:46:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我懂它。从别的角度，但依然危险\N{\rEn}I see it. In another way, but still dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.56,1:46:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想让你想想丑女的痴情\N{\rEn}I'd like for you to think about the persistent love of an ugly woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.20,1:47:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,及不育之女如何绝不能当妻子\N{\rEn}And how a barren woman should never be a wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.39,1:47:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父！神父！\N{\rEn}Padre! Padre!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.00,1:47:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父！救救我！神父\N{\rEn}Padre! Help me! Padre!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.55,1:47:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们要带她们去那儿\N{\rEn}Where are you taking them?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.26,1:47:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们要带她们去那儿\N{\rEn}Where are you taking them?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.99,1:47:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父！神父\N{\rEn}Padre! Padre!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.88,1:47:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你今天要出行\N{\rEn}You are traveling today.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.91,1:48:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐下，这对你更好，我认为\N{\rEn}Sit down. It's better for you, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.19,1:48:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请\N{\rEn}Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.76,1:48:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父\N{\rEn}Padre.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.11,1:48:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你今天感觉如何\N{\rEn}How are you feeling today?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.75,1:48:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我确信空气肯定感觉不错\N{\rEn}I'm sure the air must feel good.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:53.43,1:48:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使你是在我们的最新监狱\N{\rEn}Even though you were in our newest prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.18,1:48:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,旧监狱对神父们甚为艰苦\N{\rEn}The old prison was very tough on the Padres.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.00,1:49:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雨，风及各方面\N{\rEn}Rain, wind and every sort.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.80,1:49:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉，对不起\N{\rEn}Sorry, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.98,1:49:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,井上大人几时到此\N{\rEn}When will Inoue Sama be here?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.24,1:49:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢！他今天不会来\N{\rEn}Oh! He's not coming today.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.50,1:49:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想他吗\N{\rEn}Do you miss him?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.28,1:49:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他对我和蔼。一日三餐\N{\rEn}He treats me kindly. Three meals a day.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.63,1:49:17.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样我的身体就会背叛我的心\N{\rEn}So that my body will betray my heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.06,1:49:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是你们的计划，不是吗\N{\rEn}It's your plan, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:20.35,1:49:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 那就是你在等待的。- 根本不是\N{\rEn}- That's what you're waiting for. - Not at all!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.80,1:49:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是\N{\rEn}No?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.77,1:49:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但今天我们在等某人\N{\rEn}But we are waiting for someone today.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.41,1:49:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,井上大人想你见见他\N{\rEn}Inoue Sama wants you to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.26,1:49:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他随时都会到此\N{\rEn}He will be here any moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.07,1:49:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是葡萄牙人，如你本人\N{\rEn}He's Portuguese, like yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.75,1:49:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们应该有很多话要谈\N{\rEn}You should have a lot to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.63,1:49:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费雷拉\N{\rEn}Ferreira?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.13,1:49:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是你所期望的吗\N{\rEn}Is it who you expected?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.02,1:50:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是你所期望的吗\N{\rEn}Is it who you expected?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.51,1:50:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想跟他谈。- 不忙\N{\rEn}- I want to talk to him. - There's no hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.81,1:50:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还早。有的是时间\N{\rEn}It is early. Plenty of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.54,1:50:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我，他知道我在这里吗\N{\rEn}Tell me. Does he know I'm here?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.19,1:50:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能告诉你，我不能谈论奉行所的事\N{\rEn}I can not tell you. I must not speak about the business of the Inquisitor's office.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.07,1:50:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是，我能告诉你，他知道你活着\N{\rEn}But, I can tell you, he knows you are alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.69,1:50:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们告诉他你弃教了\N{\rEn}Because we told him you apostatized.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.47,1:50:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在，你知他们用那些草席干啥吗？\N{\rEn}Now, do you know what they use those mats for?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.66,1:50:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不\N{\rEn}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:57.94,1:51:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看，守卫，他会对神父加佩说啥呢\N{\rEn}Look, the guard. What could he be saying to Father Garupe?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.58,1:51:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 记住这个，“如果你真是基督徒，你会弃教...\N{\rEn}- Remember this, "If you are truly a Christian, you will apostatize...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:10.50,1:51:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...而不是让他们死。”\N{\rEn}...and not let them die."
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.49,1:51:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知的，奉行官承诺，如果神父加佩弃教\N{\rEn}You know. The Inquisitor promises that if Father Garupe apostatizes.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.27,1:51:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,四人就会获释\N{\rEn}The four will be free.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:32.74,1:51:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望神父加佩同意\N{\rEn}I hope Father Garupe agrees.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.50,1:51:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我应该告诉你\N{\rEn}I should tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.10,1:51:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些基督徒已踏踩及否认其信仰\N{\rEn}These Christians already trampled and denied their faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:43.52,1:51:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在奉行所\N{\rEn}At the Inquisitor's office.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.19,1:51:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他们做了你想要的，就让他们走\N{\rEn}If they did what you wanted, then let them go!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.84,1:51:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他们走！他们做了你想要的！所以让他们走！\N{\rEn}Let them go! They did what you wanted! So let them go!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:51.00,1:51:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托！拜托！拜托！让他们走！\N{\rEn}Please! Please! Please! Let them go!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.60,1:51:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不想要他们。\N{\rEn}We don't want them.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.40,1:51:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,四农民吗？\N{\rEn}Four farmers?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.20,1:51:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海岸边的岛屿上仍有数百名天主教农民\N{\rEn}There are still hundreds of Christian peasants
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.22,1:52:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在海岸边的岛屿上\N{\rEn}on the islands off the coast.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.92,1:52:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们希望神父去否认\N{\rEn}We want the Padre to deny
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.50,1:52:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,及做他们的榜样\N{\rEn}and be an example to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.52,1:52:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 神啊求求您\N{\rEn}- God please!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.87,1:52:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弃教，弃教\N{\rEn}Apostatize, Apostatize.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:15.87,1:52:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为他们着想，主\N{\rEn}For their sake, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:17.50,1:52:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别将此留予我们\N{\rEn}Do not leave this to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:19.37,1:52:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 求求您\N{\rEn}- Please!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.76,1:52:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不\N{\rEn}No!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.66,1:52:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，不加佩，不\N{\rEn}No, no Garupe, no!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:36.58,1:52:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，不，不，不，不，不\N{\rEn}No, no, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.50,1:53:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 不\N{\rEn}- No!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.00,1:53:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不！求求您！求求您\N{\rEn}No! Please! Please!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.36,1:54:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可怕的事，可怕的\N{\rEn}Terrible business. Terrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.51,1:54:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无论你目睹它多少次\N{\rEn}No matter how many times you see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.50,1:54:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想想这苦难...\N{\rEn}Think about the suffering...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.33,1:54:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...你给这些人所造成的\N{\rEn}...You have inflicted on these people!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.90,1:54:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只因你自私的梦想...\N{\rEn}Just because of your selfish dream of...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.48,1:54:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...一个基督徒的日本\N{\rEn}...a Christian Japan.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.35,1:54:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的上帝惩罚日本...\N{\rEn}Your Deus punishes Japan...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.50,1:54:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...通过你\N{\rEn}...through you!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:19.47,1:54:22.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至少加佩是干净的\N{\rEn}At least Garupe was clean,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.80,1:54:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你\N{\rEn}but you!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.34,1:54:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你毫无决心\N{\rEn}You have no will.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:26.37,1:54:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不配被称为传教士\N{\rEn}You do not deserve to be called a priest.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:06.43,1:55:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亲爱的神，亲爱的神，你为何抛弃我\N{\rEn}Dear God, dear God, why have you forsaken me?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.58,1:55:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为何抛弃我\N{\rEn}Why have you forsaken me?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:12.06,1:55:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是您的儿子\N{\rEn}I was your son.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:16.84,1:55:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您走上十字架的儿子\N{\rEn}Your son who went up to the cross.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.04,1:55:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所给予他的沉默\N{\rEn}The silent given to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.50,1:55:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有此岛残酷吗？沉默\N{\rEn}Is this island cold? Silent?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.45,1:55:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢，不，不\N{\rEn}Oh, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.25,1:55:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可笑的？可笑的！\N{\rEn}Ludicrous? Ludicrous!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.28,1:55:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,愚蠢的？\N{\rEn}Stupid?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.28,1:55:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,愚蠢的！\N{\rEn}Stupid!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.60,1:55:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不会回复的\N{\rEn}He's not going to answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:56.01,1:55:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不会回复的\N{\rEn}He's not going to answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:09.15,1:56:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要我让你进去吗\N{\rEn}Do you want me to let you in?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:13.83,1:56:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迟早\N{\rEn}In time.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:31.97,1:56:32.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父\N{\rEn}Padre.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:33.97,1:56:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父\N{\rEn}Padre.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.66,1:56:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父\N{\rEn}Padre!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:11.61,1:57:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧，神父\N{\rEn}Come along, Padre.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.97,1:57:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们传教士(指和尚)不喜欢你们传教士\N{\rEn}Our priests do not like your priests,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:27.58,1:57:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你仍能在此找到很多意义\N{\rEn}but you will still find much of value here.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:55.18,1:57:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是什么呢？神父\N{\rEn}What is it, Padre?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:59.46,1:58:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,香\N{\rEn}The incense?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.15,1:58:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肉的气息\N{\rEn}The smell of meat?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:07.59,1:58:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你吃过肉吗，自从你来到日本\N{\rEn}Have you had any meat, since you came to Japan?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:10.69,1:58:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不太喜欢自己的气味\N{\rEn}I don't much like the smell myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:19.80,1:58:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还没猜到？\N{\rEn}Have you guessed yet?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:23.20,1:58:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你猜到谁要来吗？\N{\rEn}Have you guessed who's coming?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:28.60,1:58:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是井上大人的命令\N{\rEn}This is Inoue Sama's command.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:33.13,1:58:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也是那人的愿望\N{\rEn}And the others wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:39.38,1:58:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那人\N{\rEn}The other?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:54.00,1:58:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 神父，想想你能拯救的灵魂\N{\rEn}- Padre, think of the souls you can save.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:59.00,1:59:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 神父费雷拉\N{\rEn}- Padre Ferreira
Dialogue: 0,1:59:01.80,1:59:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 封住那儿\N{\rEn}- Hold there!
Dialogue: 0,2:00:08.88,2:00:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神.. 神父\N{\rEn}Fa.. Father.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:21.49,2:00:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父费雷拉\N{\rEn}Father Ferreira.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:26.72,2:00:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我放弃了\N{\rEn}I've given up.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:32.93,2:00:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经很久未见了\N{\rEn}So long since we have met.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:38.31,2:00:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不说点啥\N{\rEn}Would you say something?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:42.35,2:00:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,啥...\N{\rEn}What...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:45.37,2:00:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能对你说啥？此种场合\N{\rEn}Can I say to you on such an occasion?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:52.87,2:00:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如你对我有丝毫同情，说点啥\N{\rEn}If you have any pity for me, say something.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:06.20,2:01:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你已，你已... 你已在此住了很久了吗\N{\rEn}Have you, have you... have you been living here for long?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:12.45,2:01:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大约一年，我以为\N{\rEn}About a year, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:22.32,2:01:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 这是啥地方？\N{\rEn}- What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:24.10,2:01:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 一座庙，我学习之处\N{\rEn}- A temple. Where I study.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:31.27,2:01:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也在狱中\N{\rEn}I'm also in a prison.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:33.50,2:01:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在长崎某地\N{\rEn}Somewhere in Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:35.40,2:01:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知确切位置\N{\rEn}I don't know precisely where.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:38.59,2:01:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知\N{\rEn}I know.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:44.06,2:01:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是我的导师\N{\rEn}You are my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:48.56,2:01:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你曾是我的忏悔师，我的导师\N{\rEn}- You were my confessor, my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:52.36,2:01:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我几乎一样\N{\rEn}- I'm much the same.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:04.00,2:02:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做件简单的事\N{\rEn}Do a single simple thing.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:06.50,2:02:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟我说，神父\N{\rEn}Tell me, Padre.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:09.70,2:02:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟我说你同意\N{\rEn}Tell me you agreed.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:26.21,2:02:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是？我是真的显得如此不同？\N{\rEn}Do I? Do I really seem so different?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:37.12,2:02:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尊敬的泽野大人每天都在书写\N{\rEn}The honorable Sawano spends his days writing...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:40.75,2:02:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...关于天文学\N{\rEn}...about astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:43.47,2:02:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,井上大人的命令\N{\rEn}Inoue Sama's order.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:45.47,2:02:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里有丰富的知识\N{\rEn}There is great knowledge here
Dialogue: 0,2:02:50.28,2:02:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但医学和天文学仍有很多要教\N{\rEn}but in Medicine and Astronomy much remains to be taught.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:53.80,2:02:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很乐意帮忙\N{\rEn}I'm happy to help.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:56.72,2:02:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欣慰的是...\N{\rEn}It is fulfilling to...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:59.80,2:03:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...终于对这个国家有用了\N{\rEn}...finally be of use in this country.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:06.00,2:03:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你快乐吗？神父\N{\rEn}And you're happy, Father?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:11.98,2:03:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我那样说了\N{\rEn}I said so.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:19.83,2:03:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说起你正在写的另一本书\N{\rEn}Mention the other book you are writing.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:25.10,2:03:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叫作《显伪录》\N{\rEn}It is called <i>Kengiroku.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:25.10,2:03:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a12}\N{\rTop_cn}注：<i>Kengiroku {\rEn}http://www.worldcat.org/title/kengiroku-disclosure-of-falsehoods/oclc/122712825)
Dialogue: 0,2:03:27.80,2:03:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它展示了基督教的时代\N{\rEn}It shows the eras of Christianity
Dialogue: 0,2:03:30.20,2:03:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,及驳斥那些教义\N{\rEn}and refutes the teachings of those.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:32.40,2:03:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你理解标题吗？\N{\rEn}Do you understand the title?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:36.56,2:03:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉他\N{\rEn}Tell him.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:41.63,2:03:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它意味着...\N{\rEn}It means...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:44.03,2:03:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...欺骗，披露或揭穿...\N{\rEn}...deceit, disclosed or unmasked...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:47.50,2:03:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...如你喜欢一个更华丽的读法\N{\rEn}...if you prefer a more florid reading.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:51.95,2:03:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连奉行官，他...\N{\rEn}There's also the Inquisitor, he...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:55.00,2:03:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...赞美它，他说它写得很好\N{\rEn}...praises it, he says it is well done.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:01.21,2:04:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 这是真的。\N{\rEn}- It's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:02.20,2:04:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你用真的当毒药\N{\rEn}You use the truth like poison.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:04.70,2:04:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,传教士这样说多滑稽啊\N{\rEn}What a funny thing for a priest to say.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:07.00,2:04:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是残酷的，残酷!\N{\rEn}This is cruel. Cruel!
Dialogue: 0,2:04:10.00,2:04:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,此举比用任意酷刑扭曲一个人的灵魂更坏\N{\rEn}Worse than any torture to twist a man's soul in this way
Dialogue: 0,2:04:14.03,2:04:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得你定是在说你自己...\N{\rEn}I think you must speaking of yourself...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:17.03,2:04:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...而非泽野忠庵\N{\rEn}...not of Sawano Chūan.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:18.50,2:04:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁\N{\rEn}Who?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:19.92,2:04:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他！他对你只是费雷拉\N{\rEn}Him! He is Ferreira only to you.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:23.26,2:04:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他如今叫泽野忠庵\N{\rEn}He is Sawano Chūan now.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:27.04,2:04:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个找到安宁的男人\N{\rEn}A man who has found peace.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:29.52,2:04:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他引导你走他的路\N{\rEn}Let him guide you along his path.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:32.39,2:04:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,慈悲之路\N{\rEn}The path of mercy.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:34.55,2:04:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那只意味着你放弃自我\N{\rEn}That means only your abandoned self.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:36.40,2:04:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人能左右别人的灵魂\N{\rEn}No one should interfere with another man's spirit.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:40.00,2:04:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帮助他人，这是佛的方式\N{\rEn}To help others, is the way of the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:43.41,2:04:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而你们的方式亦然\N{\rEn}And your way too,
Dialogue: 0,2:04:45.00,2:04:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两种宗教在这方面是同样的\N{\rEn}The two religions are the same in this.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:47.57,2:04:51.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无需争取任何人到一边或另一边...\N{\rEn}It is not necessary to win anyone over to one side or another...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:51.43,2:04:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...当分享如此之多时\N{\rEn}...when there is so much to share.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:54.21,2:04:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,继续\N{\rEn}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:59.50,2:05:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人告诉我，让你放弃信仰\N{\rEn}I've been told to get you to abandon the faith.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:06.50,2:05:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 这个...\N{\rEn}- This...
Dialogue: 0,2:05:10.50,2:05:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 这个来自“穴吊”\N{\rEn}- This is from the Pit.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:15.22,2:05:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你被紧绑，因此你不能动\N{\rEn}You're tied, so you can't move.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:18.10,2:05:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后倒吊\N{\rEn}And hung upside down.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:22.50,2:05:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弄个切口\N{\rEn}An incision is made.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:29.35,2:05:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你感到血液滴下\N{\rEn}You feel the blood dripping down.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:32.20,2:05:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一滴连一滴\N{\rEn}Drop by drop.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:34.11,2:05:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以它不会流到你头上...\N{\rEn}So it doesn't run to your head...
Dialogue: 0,2:05:36.80,2:05:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...你不会死得太快\N{\rEn}...and you won't die too soon.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:51.30,2:05:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,踏上你的圣像\N{\rEn}Step on your Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:38.26,2:06:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今你是此地最后一个传教士，神父\N{\rEn}You are the last priest left here now, Padre.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:41.33,2:06:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我确信井上大人定会高兴的把...\N{\rEn}- I'm sure Inoue Sama will be pleased to put
Dialogue: 0,2:06:43.83,2:06:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...后继者穴吊\N{\rEn}...an heir to the Pit.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:46.50,2:06:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是个务实的人，神父\N{\rEn}He is a practical man, Padre.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:49.00,2:06:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而非残酷者\N{\rEn}Not a cruel one.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:51.32,2:06:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我苦撑于此国长达15年\N{\rEn}I have labored in this country for 15 years.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:54.62,2:06:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我了解它多过你\N{\rEn}I know it better than you.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:56.99,2:07:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的宗教扎不了根\N{\rEn}Our religion does not take root...
Dialogue: 0,2:07:00.20,2:07:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...在这个国家\N{\rEn}...in this country.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:01.20,2:07:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为树根已经被磨烂了\N{\rEn}Because the roots have been torn up.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:04.20,2:07:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，因为这国家是个沼泽\N{\rEn}No. Because this country is a swamp.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:07.12,2:07:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里长不了东西\N{\rEn}Nothing grows here.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:08.22,2:07:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,植物尚为幼苗根即腐烂\N{\rEn}Plant is sapling here and the roots rot.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:10.76,2:07:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天主教在此有过生长及繁茂的时候\N{\rEn}There was a time when Christianity here grew and flourished here.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:13.58,2:07:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,何时？\N{\rEn}When?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:14.30,2:07:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,何时？在你的时代，神父\N{\rEn}When? In your time, Father.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:19.50,2:07:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你的时代，在你变得像...\N{\rEn}In your time, before you became like...
Dialogue: 0,2:07:22.00,2:07:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,象谁？象他们\N{\rEn}Like who, like them?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:24.19,2:07:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗德里格斯，请听着\N{\rEn}Rodriguez, please listen.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:26.20,2:07:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,日本人只相信他们所扭曲的...\N{\rEn}The Japanese only believe in their distortion...
Dialogue: 0,2:07:29.00,2:07:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...我们的真理，因此他们根本不信\N{\rEn}...Of our gospel. So they did not believe at all.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:31.50,2:07:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们从未信过\N{\rEn}They never believed.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:32.76,2:07:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎能如此说这些？\N{\rEn}How can you say that?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:33.60,2:07:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从圣·弗朗西斯·泽维尔时代到你自己的时代\N{\rEn}From the time of St. Francis Xavier through your own time.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:36.65,2:07:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有过成千上万的皈依者在此\N{\rEn}There were hundreds of thousands of converts here.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:39.21,2:07:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成百的？\N{\rEn}Hundreds?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:40.35,2:07:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,皈依者，是的\N{\rEn}Converts, yes!
Dialogue: 0,2:07:41.32,2:07:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗朗西斯·泽维尔来这里教日本人关于神之子...\N{\rEn}Francis Xavier came here to teach the Japanese about the son of God...
Dialogue: 0,2:07:45.18,2:07:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...但首先，他必须问如何提到神\N{\rEn}...but first he had to ask how to refer to God.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:49.00,2:07:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大日，他被告知\N{\rEn}DaiNiChi, he was told.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:51.87,2:07:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要我告诉你他们的大日吗？\N{\rEn}Shall I show you their DaiNiChi?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:55.50,2:07:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看吧\N{\rEn}Behold.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:57.25,2:08:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神之子在那儿\N{\rEn}There is the son of God.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:00.55,2:08:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神只有一个儿子\N{\rEn}God's only begotten son.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:03.95,2:08:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在圣经中，耶稣在第三天复活\N{\rEn}In the scriptures, Jesus rose on the third day.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:07.20,2:08:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在日本，神的儿子...\N{\rEn}In Japan the son of God...
Dialogue: 0,2:08:10.24,2:08:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...每天升起\N{\rEn}...rises daily.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:12.24,2:08:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,日本人想不出一种超越自然界的存在\N{\rEn}The Japanese can not think of an existence beyond the realm of nature.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:16.49,2:08:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对他们来说，没有什么能超越人类\N{\rEn}For them nothing transcends to human.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:19.12,2:08:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不\N{\rEn}No!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:19.45,2:08:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们无法构想我们的天主教之神的理念\N{\rEn}They can't conceive of our idea of the Christian God!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:22.64,2:08:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，你错了，你错了\N{\rEn}No, you're wrong. You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:24.51,2:08:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们敬拜神！神！我们的主\N{\rEn}They worship God! God! Our Lord!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:28.28,2:08:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们赞美耶稣之名\N{\rEn}They praise the name of Deus!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:30.40,2:08:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那只是神的另一个名字，他们从不知道\N{\rEn}That's just another name for a God, they never knew.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:34.53,2:08:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看到人死了\N{\rEn}I saw men die!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:36.00,2:08:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也看到了\N{\rEn}I did too.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:37.15,2:08:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为耶稣！\N{\rEn}For Deus!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:38.50,2:08:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与他们的信仰烧在一起\N{\rEn}On fire with their faith.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:40.80,2:08:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的烈士可能烧着了，神父\N{\rEn}Your martyrs might have been on fire, Father.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:43.51,2:08:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但那不是基督徒的信仰\N{\rEn}But it was not of the Christian faith.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:46.68,2:08:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我目睹他们死去，我目睹他们死去，他们不是为虚无而死\N{\rEn}I saw them die. I saw them die. They did not die for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:51.24,2:08:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不是\N{\rEn}They did not.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:54.00,2:08:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们为你而死，罗德里格斯\N{\rEn}They're dying for you, Rodriguez.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:01.00,2:09:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你救了多少\N{\rEn}How many did you save?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:03.23,2:09:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你踏踩我们主之脸之时\N{\rEn}When you trampled on the face of our Lord?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:05.50,2:09:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你自己身边有多少人\N{\rEn}How many beside yourself?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:07.76,2:09:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道\N{\rEn}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:09.20,2:09:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然不象你可能救的那么多\N{\rEn}Certainly not as many as you may help.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:12.18,2:09:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你试图为自己的弱点辩护\N{\rEn}You're trying to justify your own weakness.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:16.00,2:09:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,愿神怜悯你！\N{\rEn}God have mercy on you!
Dialogue: 0,2:09:18.00,2:09:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪个神？哪一位？\N{\rEn}Which God? Which one?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:20.20,2:09:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们说，山...\N{\rEn}We say Sangewalede...
Dialogue: 0,2:09:24.50,2:09:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很抱歉，实际上你尚未学过此语言，是吗\N{\rEn}I'm sorry, you haven't learned the language though really, have you?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:27.81,2:09:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这儿有句俗话\N{\rEn}There is a saying here
Dialogue: 0,2:09:30.20,2:09:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,江山易改\N{\rEn}Mountains and rivers can be moved.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:32.50,2:09:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本性难易\N{\rEn}But man's nature can not be moved.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:35.41,2:09:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这很睿智，像极此处\N{\rEn}It's very wise, like so much here.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:39.60,2:09:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在日本找到了我们的本性，罗德里格斯\N{\rEn}We find our original nature in Japan, Rodriguez.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:45.22,2:09:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许是通过找寻神而被领悟\N{\rEn}Perhaps this was meant by finding God.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:50.06,2:09:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是个耻辱\N{\rEn}You're a disgrace.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:56.62,2:09:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是个耻辱，神父\N{\rEn}You're a disgrace, Father.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:00.08,2:10:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能\N{\rEn}I can't.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:02.29,2:10:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我再也不能那样叫你了\N{\rEn}I can't even call you that anymore.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:06.79,2:10:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\rEn}Good.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:08.35,2:10:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我如今有了日本名\N{\rEn}I have a Japanese name now.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:12.00,2:10:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一位妻子及孩子\N{\rEn}A wife and children.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:17.09,2:10:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我全继承了她们，从一名被处决者那里\N{\rEn}I inherited them all from an executed man.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:35.81,2:10:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你觉得如何？\N{\rEn}- How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,2:10:37.11,2:10:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 他已向你展示仁慈之路\N{\rEn}- He has shown you the path of mercy.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:40.49,2:10:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我希望你接受它\N{\rEn}- I hope you take it.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:43.90,2:10:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你何不就吊我入穴？\N{\rEn}Why don't you just hang me in the pit?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:07.00,2:11:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你被奉行所传唤\N{\rEn}You are called to the Inquisitor's office.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:19.36,2:11:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父，你为他们来到这儿，而他们都恨你\N{\rEn}Padre, you came here for them and they all hate you.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:23.84,2:11:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽情侮辱我，这只会给我更多勇气\N{\rEn}Insult me all you like, it just give me more courage.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:27.80,2:11:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今晚你会需要它\N{\rEn}You will need it tonight.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:30.74,2:11:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是个好男人，神父。你受不了苦难。但你错了，对别人来说\N{\rEn}You are a good man, Padre. You can not stand suffering. You're wrong, for others.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:41.16,2:11:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,井上大人说你今晚会成为一个弃教者\N{\rEn}Inoue Sama says you will be a apostatize tonight.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:46.21,2:11:47.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他对费雷拉是对的...\N{\rEn}He was right about Ferreira...
Dialogue: 0,2:11:49.00,2:11:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...他对你也是对的\N{\rEn}...and he's right about you.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:49.20,2:11:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赞美他(拉丁语)\N{\rEn}{\a6}\N{\rEn}LauDate Eum
Dialogue: 0,2:11:55.50,2:11:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神帮帮我。耶稣帮帮我\N{\rEn}God help me. Jesus help me.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:05.32,2:12:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在果园里，您说过\N{\rEn}In the garden, you said
Dialogue: 0,2:12:07.32,2:12:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“您的灵魂是悲伤的，甚至接近死亡。”\N{\rEn}"Thy soul is sorrowful even unto death."\N{\rTop_cn}(马太福音，26章38节，此处比原文少了些词。果园，指Gethsemane，客西马尼园，耶稣蒙被犹大出卖之地)
Dialogue: 0,2:12:12.20,2:12:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会为您流血，我会...\N{\rEn}I would bleed for you, I would...
Dialogue: 0,2:12:16.20,2:12:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会为您去死\N{\rEn}I would die for you.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:18.40,2:12:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若我了解您\N{\rEn}If I knew you.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:21.18,2:12:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您与我同在于此吗\N{\rEn}Are you here with me?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:40.83,2:12:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父\N{\rEn}Padre.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:43.00,2:12:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原谅我\N{\rEn}Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:46.13,2:12:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父\N{\rEn}Padre.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:47.50,2:12:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要做忏悔\N{\rEn}I came to make confession!
Dialogue: 0,2:12:50.38,2:12:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父\N{\rEn}Padre!
Dialogue: 0,2:12:53.58,2:12:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原谅我，神父\N{\rEn}Forgive me, Padre!
Dialogue: 0,2:13:05.81,2:13:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阻止它！阻止它！阻止它！阻止噪声\N{\rEn}Stop it! Stop it! Stop it! Stop the noise!
Dialogue: 0,2:13:09.61,2:13:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阻止它！来人帮帮他\N{\rEn}Stop it! Someone help him!
Dialogue: 0,2:13:13.41,2:13:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要什么\N{\rEn}What do you need?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:14.88,2:13:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是我，那下边\N{\rEn}Not me, down there.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:16.58,2:13:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人受痛苦\N{\rEn}there is a man in agony!
Dialogue: 0,2:13:18.40,2:13:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,守卫在酣睡还打着鼾，像只野狗\N{\rEn}And the guard is sound asleep and snoring like a wild dog!
Dialogue: 0,2:13:22.97,2:13:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你以为那噪声是守卫\N{\rEn}You think that noise is the guard?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:26.00,2:13:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难以置信\N{\rEn}Incredible!
Dialogue: 0,2:13:27.56,2:13:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泽野！告诉他，说它是啥\N{\rEn}Sawa! Tell him, say what it is.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:30.98,2:13:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它不是守卫也不是打鼾\N{\rEn}It is not the guard and it's not snoring.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:36.00,2:13:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是基督徒\N{\rEn}It's Christians.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:37.50,2:13:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们五个，事实上\N{\rEn}Five of them in fact.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:39.20,2:13:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全被吊在穴里\N{\rEn}All hanging in the pit.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:46.35,2:13:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你找到墙上的话了吗\N{\rEn}Have you found the words on the wall?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:50.10,2:13:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赞美他(拉丁语)\N{\rEn}LauDaTe E u m
Dialogue: 0,2:13:52.75,2:13:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赞美他\N{\rEn}Praise him.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:56.14,2:13:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我用石头刻下它们，当我此牢房时...\N{\rEn}I cut them there with a stone when I was in this cell...
Dialogue: 0,2:13:59.77,2:14:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...跟你一样\N{\rEn}...like you
Dialogue: 0,2:14:05.72,2:14:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,闭嘴\N{\rEn}Be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:07.07,2:14:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要，不要跟我说，你没权力跟我说\N{\rEn}Don't, don't speak to me, you have no right to speak to me.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:10.00,2:14:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢，我有，因为你就像我\N{\rEn}Oh, I do, because you were just like me.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:12.73,2:14:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看到耶稣及客西马尼园，相信你的考验和他的一样\N{\rEn}You see Jesus and Gethsemane believe that your trial is the same as his.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:17.27,2:14:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,穴吊的苦难远远不及耶稣所受\N{\rEn}That's far from the Pit of suffering too just like Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:19.72,2:14:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而这些人没有你的骄傲\N{\rEn}but they don't have your pride.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:21.55,2:14:24.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们永远不会把自己同耶稣相比\N{\rEn}They would never compare themselves to Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:24.60,2:14:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有权利吗？让他们受苦？\N{\rEn}Do you have the right? To make them suffer?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:28.52,2:14:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在此牢听过这般苦难的痛苦\N{\rEn}I heard the cries of suffering in this same cell.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:31.54,2:14:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,于是我做了\N{\rEn}And I acted.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:32.30,2:14:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你原谅自己，你原谅自己\N{\rEn}You excuse yourself, you excuse yourself,
Dialogue: 0,2:14:34.30,2:14:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是黑暗之灵\N{\rEn}that is the spirit of darkness!
Dialogue: 0,2:14:37.24,2:14:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会为他们做啥？祈祷吗？\N{\rEn}What would you do for them? Pray?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:41.00,2:14:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又得到什么回应？\N{\rEn}And get what in return?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:43.50,2:14:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有更多的苦难\N{\rEn}Only more suffering.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:45.32,2:14:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯你能结束的苦难，不是神！- 离我远点！\N{\rEn}A suffering only you can end, not God! - Go away from me.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:50.93,2:14:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也祷告，罗德里格斯\N{\rEn}I pray too, Rodriguez.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:54.30,2:14:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那没用\N{\rEn}It doesn't help.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:57.57,2:14:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,继续\N{\rEn}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:59.50,2:15:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祷告\N{\rEn}Pray.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:06.40,2:15:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但要睁眼祷告\N{\rEn}But pray with your eyes open.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:26.67,2:15:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以赦免他们\N{\rEn}You can spare them.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:29.10,2:15:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们呼唤救命，就像你呼唤神\N{\rEn}They call out for help, just as you call to God.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:31.82,2:15:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他沉默，而你不必\N{\rEn}He is silent and you do not have to be.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:34.40,2:15:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们该弃教！弃教\N{\rEn}They should apostatize! Apostatize!
Dialogue: 0,2:15:37.48,2:15:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神救我，弃教\N{\rEn}God help me, apostatize!
Dialogue: 0,2:15:41.22,2:15:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他们已弃教\N{\rEn}But they have apostatized.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:43.50,2:15:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多次\N{\rEn}Many times over.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:45.50,2:15:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们因你在此，罗德里格斯\N{\rEn}They're here for you, Rodriguez!
Dialogue: 0,2:15:47.84,2:15:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要你不放弃信仰，他们就不能获救\N{\rEn}As long as you don't apostatize, they can not be saved.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:50.83,2:15:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,传教士应该效仿基督\N{\rEn}A priest should act in imitation of Christ.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:54.13,2:15:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果基督在此。\N{\rEn}If Christ were here.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:57.50,2:15:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基督在此\N{\rEn}Christ were here.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:59.60,2:16:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会做的\N{\rEn}He would have acted.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:01.40,2:16:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为他们着想弃教\N{\rEn}Apostatized for their sake.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:05.00,2:16:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，不，他在这儿，基督在这儿，我只是听不到他\N{\rEn}No. No, he's here, Christ is here. I just can't hear him.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:08.05,2:16:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给神看你爱他\N{\rEn}Show God you love him!
Dialogue: 0,2:16:10.10,2:16:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,救他所爱者之命\N{\rEn}Save the lives of the people he loves!
Dialogue: 0,2:16:14.23,2:16:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有东西...\N{\rEn}There is something...
Dialogue: 0,2:16:16.20,2:16:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...比教会的审判更为重要\N{\rEn}...more important than the judgement of the Church.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:21.95,2:16:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你如今将去完成...\N{\rEn}You are now going to fulfill...
Dialogue: 0,2:16:24.19,2:16:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...最痛苦且从未被履行过的慈悲之举\N{\rEn}...the most painful act of love that has ever been performed.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:47.17,2:16:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只是形式，只是形式\N{\rEn}It's only a formality. Just a formality.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:24.75,2:17:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>现在来吧\N{\rEn}Come ahead now.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:28.30,2:17:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>这没什么\N{\rEn}It's alright.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:31.60,2:17:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>踏踩我\N{\rEn}Step on me.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:37.00,2:17:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>我理解你的痛苦\N{\rEn}I understand your pain.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:42.55,2:17:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>我生于这世上...\N{\rEn}I was born into this world...
Dialogue: 0,2:17:44.70,2:17:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>...就为分担人痛苦\N{\rEn}...to share men's pain.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:48.28,2:17:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>我背负这十字架...\N{\rEn}I carried this cross...
Dialogue: 0,2:17:50.40,2:17:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>...免除你们的痛苦\N{\rEn}...for your pain.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:56.46,2:17:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>你命现与我同在\N{\rEn}Your life is with me now.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:02.24,2:18:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>踏{\fad(3000,100)}吧\N{\rEn}Step.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:26.61,2:19:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“弃教的保罗”\N{\rEn}"Apostate Paul!"
Dialogue: 0,2:19:28.11,2:19:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“弃教的保罗”\N{\rEn}"Apostate Paul!"
Dialogue: 0,2:19:35.90,2:19:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>那是在1641年...\N{\rEn}<i>It was in the year 1641...
Dialogue: 0,2:19:39.50,2:19:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...在我首次航海旅日期间\N{\rEn}<i>...during the first of my voyages to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:43.75,2:19:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>我，迪特尔·阿尔博瑞奇...\N{\rEn}<i>That I, Dieter Albritch...
Dialogue: 0,2:19:46.25,2:19:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...发现了最特别的事...\N{\rEn}<i>...came upon the most extraordinary story
Dialogue: 0,2:19:48.60,2:19:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...在这些纸页中\N{\rEn}<i>...in these pages.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:52.18,2:19:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天主教\N{\rEn}Christian.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:54.30,2:19:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非天主教\N{\rEn}Unchristian.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:56.13,2:19:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>作为一家伟大的荷兰贸易公司的医生...\N{\rEn}<i>As a physician in a great Dutch trading company...
Dialogue: 0,2:19:59.13,2:20:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...我四处旅行\N{\rEn}<i>...I traveled widely.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:01.69,2:20:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天主教\N{\rEn}Christian.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:03.61,2:20:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>然而没有任何一桩我所详述于此日记的奇观...\N{\rEn}<i>But none of the wonders I have recounted in this journal...
Dialogue: 0,2:20:07.11,2:20:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...被如此评论...\N{\rEn}<i>...has been so commented on...
Dialogue: 0,2:20:09.60,2:20:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...作为稀奇事件...\N{\rEn}<i>...as the curious matter...
Dialogue: 0,2:20:12.80,2:20:15.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...弃教传教士的\N{\rEn}<i>...of the apostatized priests.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:15.93,2:20:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天主教\N{\rEn}Christian.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:18.20,2:20:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>我比任何欧洲记者更接近此国之谜\N{\rEn}<i>I came closer than any European chronicler to the enigma of this country.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:24.77,2:20:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非天主教\N{\rEn}Unchristian.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:26.61,2:20:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...及学习失联传教士的生活\N{\rEn}<i>...and to learning of the lives of the lost priests.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:32.44,2:20:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>在某种程度上，奉行官，会突袭住宅...\N{\rEn}<i>In a way, the Inquisitor, would raid homes...
Dialogue: 0,2:20:36.00,2:20:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...并搜查任何藏有天主教图像之物\N{\rEn}<i>...and search for any objects with hidden Christian images.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:41.36,2:20:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天主教\N{\rEn}Christian.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:44.98,2:20:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>两位传教士被要求检查这些东西，并核实它们的用途\N{\rEn}<i>The two priests were required to examine these things, and verify their use.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:52.28,2:20:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>我甚至偶尔，亲自观察它们\N{\rEn}<i>I even on occasion, observed them myself.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:59.44,2:21:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>荷兰人是唯一被允许在日本进行贸易的欧洲人\N{\rEn}<i>The Dutch were the only Europeans allowed to trade in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:04.11,2:21:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>所有船支被搜查，以确保他们不走私宗教物品\N{\rEn}<i>All ships were searched to warrant they were not smuggling religious objects.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:10.13,2:21:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>没有任何带有十字、圣人图像的东西或念珠能通过\N{\rEn}<i>Nothing bearing the images of the cross, the saint or rosary could pass.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:31.56,2:21:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>尽管每次必查，少数物品难免被走私进来\N{\rEn}<i>Despite every attempt, a few things inevitably were smuggled in.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:36.44,2:21:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>天主教\N{\rEn}<i>Christian.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:42.86,2:21:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>然后它就会使日本人痛苦，仿佛血已溢出\N{\rEn}<i>And then it was as distressing to the Japanese, as if blood had been spilled.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:59.71,2:22:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们被教导要爱那些跟我们不和者\N{\rEn}We were taught to love those who discord us.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:04.69,2:22:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对他们毫无感觉\N{\rEn}I feel nothing for them.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:07.26,2:22:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有我们的主能审判你的心\N{\rEn}Only our Lord can judge your heart.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:13.37,2:22:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说，我们的主\N{\rEn}You said our Lord.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:22.59,2:22:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怀疑\N{\rEn}I doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:30.89,2:22:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>泽野忠庵死后，另一位传教士承担了其职责\N{\rEn}<i>When Sawano Chūan died, the other priests assumed his duties.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:35.75,2:22:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>并以区别对待他们\N{\rEn}<i>And performed them with distinction.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:41.93,2:22:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>但是这次，我观察到一个相当大的语言技巧\N{\rEn}<i>But this time, I observed yet a quite considerable skill with the language.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:48.57,2:22:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>且似乎对他的处境很满意\N{\rEn}<i>And seemed to be at peace with his situation.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:54.35,2:22:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有个好消息\N{\rEn}I have good news.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:56.50,2:22:59.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,江户有人死了\N{\rEn}A man has died in Edo.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:59.76,2:23:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冈田三右卫门\N{\rEn}Okada Sanyemon.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:02.29,2:23:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你将继承其名字\N{\rEn}You will take his name.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:04.81,2:23:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像他一样\N{\rEn}Just as he did.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:07.30,2:23:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有一个家庭，妻子，儿子\N{\rEn}He had a household and wife and son.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:12.18,2:23:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以把她当作你的妻子\N{\rEn}You can take her as your wife.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:15.77,2:23:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,男人工作得最好当他不再单身时\N{\rEn}A man works best when he's not alone.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:21.12,2:23:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应当知道这岛上的生月和五岛\N{\rEn}You should know that on the islands of Ikitsuki and Goto.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:30.21,2:23:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仍有许多农民自以为是基督徒\N{\rEn}There are still many farmers who think themselves as Christian.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:35.02,2:23:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你喜欢那样吧？他们可以继续当基督徒\N{\rEn}You like that? They can continue to be Christian.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:39.07,2:23:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可能会对此感到满意\N{\rEn}You may take some satisfaction in that.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:42.68,2:23:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为根被砍断了\N{\rEn}Because the roots are cut.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:47.99,2:23:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沼泽里长不了任何东西\N{\rEn}Nothing grows in a swamp.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:52.25,2:23:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的，日本就是那种国家\N{\rEn}Yes, Japan is that kind of country.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:56.10,2:23:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那宗教，那些你带给我们的基督徒\N{\rEn}The religion, the Christian you brought us
Dialogue: 0,2:23:59.47,2:24:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已成为奇怪的东西，它变了\N{\rEn}has became a strange thing. It's changed.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:19.85,2:24:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不是败给我\N{\rEn}You were not defeated by me.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:22.50,2:24:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你败给了日本这个沼泽\N{\rEn}You were defeated by this swamp of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:29.89,2:24:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎\N{\rEn}Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:34.39,2:24:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>冈田三右卫门住进江户\N{\rEn}<i>Okada Sanyemon lived in Edo
Dialogue: 0,2:24:37.39,2:24:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>度过他的余生\N{\rEn}<i>for the remaining years of his life.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:40.65,2:24:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>大约10年后，我获准访问江户\N{\rEn}<i>Some 10 years later, I was allowed to visit Edo.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:45.15,2:24:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>日本人随意地闲聊了冈田三右卫门\N{\rEn}<i>The Japanese gossiped freely about Okada Sanyemon.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:49.70,2:24:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>奉行官井上再三要求他的弃教誓言\N{\rEn}<i>The Inquisitor Inoue demanded repeated vows of apostasy from him.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:54.66,2:25:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>他们则说，那沦落的传教士全都迅速积极的回应了他们\N{\rEn}<i>And they say, the fallen priest applied them all quickly and vigorously.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:17.30,2:25:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听说奉行官派他的人找你\N{\rEn}I heard the Inquisitor sent his men for you.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:21.25,2:25:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有麻烦吗？- 不\N{\rEn}Was there trouble? - No.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:26.10,2:25:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们只是想确保我写下那证据\N{\rEn}They only wanted to make sure I wrote that corroboration.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:30.12,2:25:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的谴责信\N{\rEn}My letters of denunciation.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:43.06,2:25:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\N{\rEn}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:45.06,2:25:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\N{\rEn}ありがとうございます
Dialogue: 0,2:25:49.00,2:25:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没有任何事需要谢我\N{\rEn}You have nothing to thank me for.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:55.73,2:25:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为在此陪我\N{\rEn}For being here with me.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:09.22,2:26:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父\N{\rEn}Padre.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:12.43,2:26:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，不，我不是\N{\rEn}No, no. I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:16.43,2:26:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不再是了\N{\rEn}I'm not anymore！
Dialogue: 0,2:26:20.51,2:26:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是个沦落的传教士\N{\rEn}I'm a fallen priest
Dialogue: 0,2:26:22.20,2:26:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你是最后一个传教士\N{\rEn}But you are the last priest left.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:26.23,2:26:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你仍能听我的忏悔\N{\rEn}You could still hear my confession.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:28.80,2:26:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不！我不能\N{\rEn}No! I can't!
Dialogue: 0,2:26:30.71,2:26:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不！我不能\N{\rEn}No! I can't!
Dialogue: 0,2:26:34.59,2:26:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我仍为我的所为痛苦，神父\N{\rEn}I still suffer for what I did, Padre.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:38.59,2:26:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我背叛了你\N{\rEn}I betrayed you.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:40.59,2:26:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我背叛了我的家人\N{\rEn}I betrayed my family.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:42.65,2:26:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我背叛了我们的主\N{\rEn}I betrayed our Lord.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:46.30,2:26:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,求您\N{\rEn}Please!
Dialogue: 0,2:26:49.80,2:26:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听我忏悔吧\N{\rEn}Hear my confession.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:54.93,2:26:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父\N{\rEn}Padre.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:15.24,2:27:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主啊，我反抗您的沉默\N{\rEn}Lord, I fought against your silence.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:24.60,2:27:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>我陪同你受苦\N{\rEn}I suffered beside you.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:27.60,2:27:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<b>我从不沉默\N{\rEn}I was never silent.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:35.09,2:27:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知\N{\rEn}I know.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:43.01,2:27:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是即使...\N{\rEn}But even...
Dialogue: 0,2:27:45.76,2:27:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...神沉默我的一生\N{\rEn}...if God had been silent my whole life.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:51.58,2:27:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在此每天\N{\rEn}To this very day.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:55.77,2:27:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事事我为，事事我已为\N{\rEn}Everything I do, everything I've done.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:04.60,2:28:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对他说话\N{\rEn}Speaks of him.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:10.04,2:28:12.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是我在沉默中听到了您的声音\N{\rEn}It was in the silence that I heard your voice.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:31.86,2:28:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>奉行官继续坚持定期查验...\N{\rEn}<i>The Inquisitor continued to insist on periodic examinations...
Dialogue: 0,2:28:36.79,2:28:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...所有疑似基督徒\N{\rEn}<i>...Of all suspected Christians.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:40.33,2:28:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>冈田三右卫门，未能从中豁免\N{\rEn}<i>Okada Sanyemon, was not exempt from this.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:44.31,2:28:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>在某种程度上，这就决定了他的榜样永远不会被遗忘\N{\rEn}<i>In a way, it was determined to never let his example be forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:49.50,2:28:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>也许尤其是...\N{\rEn}<i>Perhaps most particularly...
Dialogue: 0,2:28:52.20,2:28:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...通过传教士本人\N{\rEn}<i>...by the priest himself.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:31.26,2:29:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>在1667年，一个宗教图像在护身符中被发现\N{\rEn}<i>In the year 1667. A religious image was discovered inside an amulet.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:38.51,2:29:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>属于一名唤作吉次郎的仆人\N{\rEn}<i>Belonging to a servant called Kichijiro.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:47.87,2:29:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>仆人说他是在赌博中赢得，从未看过里面\N{\rEn}<i>The servant said he had won at gambling. Had never looked inside.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:52.95,2:29:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>且从未从冈田三右卫门处得到此护身符\N{\rEn}<i>And could never have gotten the amulet from Okada Sanyemon.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:56.71,2:29:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>因为他总是在看守下\N{\rEn}<i>Since he was always under guard.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:05.06,2:30:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>此仆人，吉次郎，被带走\N{\rEn}<i>The servant, Kichijiro, was taken away.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:11.11,2:30:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>此后，冈田三右卫门本人，被密切监视\N{\rEn}<i>After that, Okada Sanyemon himself, was carefully watched.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:16.88,2:30:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>在我最后的旅行期间，在1682，我问及他\N{\rEn}<i>During my last voyage, in 1682, I asked about him.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:21.84,2:30:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>日本人则热切回答\N{\rEn}<i>And the Japanese were eager to reply.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:25.84,2:30:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>最后的传教士从未承认天主教的神...\N{\rEn}<i>The last priest never acknowledged the Christian God...
Dialogue: 0,2:30:30.50,2:30:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>...没有通过文字或图像\N{\rEn}<i>...not by word or symbol.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:34.04,2:30:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>他从未说过他\N{\rEn}<i>He never spoke of him.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:36.18,2:30:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>且从未祷告过\N{\rEn}<i>And never prayed.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:38.41,2:30:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>甚至在他死去时\N{\rEn}<i>Not even when he died.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:41.35,2:30:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>他所信仰的事，早已结束\N{\rEn}<i>The business of his faith, was long ended.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:51.77,2:30:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>三名守卫看守棺材\N{\rEn}<i>Three guards stood watch over the coffin.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:55.40,2:30:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>直至其可被带走，只是为了被确定\N{\rEn}<i>Until it could be taken away, just to be certain.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:00.77,2:31:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>只有他的妻子被短暂允许看到遗体\N{\rEn}<i>Only his wife was briefly allowed to view the body.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:05.20,2:31:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>并把一件简陋的纪念须刀放入\N{\rEn}<i>And placed there a humble memory gatana.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:09.37,2:31:11.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>以辟开邪恶之灵\N{\rEn}<i>To ward off evil spirits.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:50.80,2:31:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>没有迹象表明她哭了\N{\rEn}<i>There was no indication that she wept.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:47.26,2:32:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>遗体以佛教的仪礼处置\N{\rEn}<i>The body was treated in the Buddhist manner.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:51.48,2:32:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>他还被赐予一个死去的法号\N{\rEn}<i>And he was given a posthumous Buddhist name.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:05.94,2:33:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>那个曾名罗德里格斯的男人\N{\rEn}<i>The man who was once Rodriguez.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:09.96,2:33:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>按他们之意结束\N{\rEn}<i>Ended as they wanted.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:13.62,2:33:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>而当我第一次看见他\N{\rEn}<i>And as I first saw him.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:17.43,2:33:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>与神失联\N{\rEn}<i>Lost to God.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:25.32,2:33:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>但是否如此\N{\rEn}<i>But as to that.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:27.60,2:33:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,<i>实际上\N{\rEn}<i>In deed.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:30.00,2:33:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有神能回答\N{\rEn}<i>Only God can answer.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:20.81,2:34:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为日本的基督徒及他们的牧师 为上帝的最大荣耀\N{\rEn}For the Japanese Christians and their pastors.For the greater glory of God.
